properties.name: testingDevices
properties.docs:
An Array of devices IDs that will be marked as tested devices if {@link AdMobInitializationOptions.initializeForTesting} is true
(Real Ads will be served to Testing devices but they will not count as 'real').

properties.name: initializeForTesting
properties.docs:
If set to true, the devices on {@link AdMobInitializationOptions.testingDevices} will
be registered to receive test production ads.

properties.name: tagForChildDirectedTreatment
properties.docs:
For purposes of the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA),
there is a setting called tagForChildDirectedTreatment.

properties.name: tagForUnderAgeOfConsent
properties.docs:
When using this feature,
a Tag For Users under the Age of Consent in Europe (TFUA) parameter will be included in all future ad requests.

properties.name: maxAdContentRating
properties.docs:
As an app developer,
you can indicate whether you want Google to treat your content as child-directed when you make an ad request.

properties.name: muted
properties.docs:
To inform the SDK that the app volume has been muted.
Note: Video ads that are ineligible to be shown with muted audio are not returned for ad requests made,
when the app volume is reported as muted or set to a value of 0. This may restrict a subset of the broader video ads pool from serving.

properties.name: volume
properties.docs:
If your app has its own volume controls (such as custom music or sound effect volumes),
disclosing app volume to the Google Mobile Ads SDK allows video ads to respect app volume settings.
enable set 0.0 - 1.0, any float allowed.

properties.name: adSize
properties.docs:
Banner Ad Size, defaults to ADAPTIVE_BANNER.
IT can be: ADAPTIVE_BANNER, SMART_BANNER, BANNER,
MEDIUM_RECTANGLE, FULL_BANNER, LEADERBOARD

properties.name: position

members.name: Loaded
members.docs: Emits after trying to prepare a RewardAd and the Video is loaded and ready to be show

members.name: FailedToLoad
members.docs: Emits after trying to prepare a RewardAd when it could not be loaded

members.name: Showed
members.docs: Emits when the AdReward video is visible to the user

members.name: FailedToShow
members.docs: Emits when the AdReward video is failed to show

members.name: Dismissed
members.docs:
Emits when the AdReward video is not visible to the user anymore.

**Important**: This has nothing to do with the reward it self. This event
will emits in this two cases:
1. The user starts the video ad but close it before the reward emit.
2. The user start the video and see it until end, then gets the reward
and after that the ad is closed.
